Imports:
    gtools,ade4,adegenet
Suggests:
    ape,
    pegas,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat
Description: Allows the estimation of hierarchical F-statistics from haploid or
    diploid genetic data with any numbers of levels in the hierarchy, following the
    algorithm of Yang (Evolution, 1998, 52(4):950-956; <http://www.jstor.org/stable/
    2411227>. Functions are also given to test via randomisations the significance
    of each F and variance components, using the likelihood-ratio statistics G
    (Goudet et al, 1996 <http://www.genetics.org/content/144/4/1933>).
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
